<doc id="1270740" wikidata="Q1940452" url="?curid=1270740" title="Königs Wusterhausen Central Tower">
<text>Königs Wusterhausen Central Tower was a , freestanding steel framework tower on the Funkerberg of Königs Wusterhausen, Germany. The tower, with its unique triangular cross section, was built from 1924 to 1925. The tower collapsed during the storm Quimburga on 13 November 1972.

