<doc id="1270808" wikidata="Q2270103" url="?curid=1270808" title="Behren-Bokel Transmitter">
<text>The Behren-Bokel Transmitter, also known as the Sprakensehl Transmitter is a 323-metre high guyed steel tube radio mast in Behren-Bokel near Uelzen in Lower Saxony, Germany. The mast is used for FM- and TV-broadcasting, and was at its erection time in 1961 the highest construction of West Germany.

==See also==
